dmca.title: DMCA Complaint from MOVADO RE: Sale of Counterfeit MOVADO watches by www.watchgem.com
dmca.body:
________________________________ From: Counterfeit MovaClient [mailto:MovaClient@fzlz.com] Posted At: Tuesday, November 14, 2006 10:40 AM Posted To: Legal Response Conversation: DMCA Complaint from MOVADO RE: Sale of Counterfeit MOVADO watches by www.watchgem.com (Our Ref: MOVA USA TS-99/11160-023) Subject: DMCA Complaint from MOVADO RE: Sale of Counterfeit MOVADO watches by www.watchgem.com (Our Ref: MOVA USA TS-99/11160-023) ThePlanet.com Internet Services, Inc. 1333 North Stemmons Freeway Suite 110 Dallas, TX 75207 Dear Sir or Madam: We represent the Movado Group of companies ("Movado"), an internationally-known manufacturer and seller of high-quality watches. Our client is the exclusive owner of many federally registered trademarks and copyrights in the U.S., as well as in other countries around the world. These include trademark registrations for the marks MOVADO in International Class 14 for watches (U.S. Reg. No. 1, 294, 171); for MUSEUM in International Class 14 for wrist watches (U.S. Reg. No. 1,114,067); for VIZIO in International Class 14 for watches (U.S. Reg. No. 2,098,170), as well as the MOVADO Museum Watch Design (U.S. Reg. Nos. 1,381,257 and 1,398,457); Movado is also the exclusive licensee of the mark ESQ. for watches (U.S. Reg. No. 1,672,563) (collectively the "MOVADO Marks"). Through many years of use, advertising and promotion, the MOVADO Marks have become closely identified with our client's business and represent substantial goodwill. It has recently come to our attention that you provide services to a web page known as www.watchgem.com, which offers for sale counterfeit and infringing watches bearing one or more of the MOVADO Marks, the MOVADO Museum Watch Design, or marks substantially indistinguishable therefrom. These items are being offered for sale in violation of federal and state trademark laws as well as related laws of unfair competition, which entitle Movado to extensive remedies, including preliminary and permanent injunctions, recovery of profits, treble damages and attorneys' fees. The Acceptable Use Policy posted on your web site prohibits trademark infringement by your customers and provides you with the power to terminate or suspend services to accounts that violate the policy. Thus, please provide confirmation by November 17, 2006 that you will immediately cease providing services to the owner of the site until all content relating to the infringing MOVADO watches is removed. In accordance with your rules regarding Notification of Claimed Infringement, we affirm that our client has a good faith belief that the use of the material in the manner complained of is not authorized by the owner and that the information in this notification is accurate. We also state under penalty of perjury that our client is the owner of the exclusive trademark rights the MOVADO mark, which are being infringed. This letter is without prejudice to our client's rights or remedies, all of which are expressly reserved. Thank you for your cooperation. Regards, Yvonne Sharpy Internet Paralegal Fross Zelnick Lehrman & Zissu, P.C. 866 United Nations Plaza New York, NY 10017 Direct: 212-813-8248 Fax: 212-813-5901 -----Original Message----- From: abuse@theplanet.com [mailto:abuse@theplanet.com] Posted At: Friday, November 10, 2006 1:52 PM Posted To: Counterfeit MovaClient Conversation: [EV1-C1764272Y] Objection to sale of counterfeit MOVADO watches Subject: [EV1-C1764272Y] Objection to sale of counterfeit MOVADO watches This is an automatic reply from Theplanet.com Network Abuse Response Center regarding the recent report that you sent.
